    "body": "## Goal\nProduce feature frames for **current WC2026 matches** \u2014 both the unplayed fixtures already present in martj42's `wc2026_schedule` (no-key path) and, optionally, the live `TournamentState` (key-gated). Reuse the core assembler (issue #9) so WC2026 features are **schema-identical** to training features. This satisfies the cycle requirement that feature frames cover both historical training matches **and** current WC2026 matches, with the no-key path fully functional and the live path strictly additive.\n\n## Context\nWC2026 is mid-group-stage; the forecast conditions on results to date. Two sources feed current state:\n- **No-key (default):** martj42 already contains the WC2026 fixture list. `worldcup_playoff/data/martj42_loader.py` exposes `wc2026_schedule(df)` which filters `TOURNAMENT == \"FIFA World Cup\"` (played + unplayed, `<NA>` goals until played). This path requires **zero network**.\n- **Key-gated (optional):** `worldcup_playoff/data/live.py` \u2014 `fetch_tournament_state(client, competition=\"WC\") -> TournamentState`. `TournamentState(played, remaining_group_fixtures, standings)`. `LiveMatch` fields: `id, utc_date, status, stage, group, home_team, away_team` (team names already crosswalk-normalized; **may be `None`** for unresolved knockout slots). `GroupStanding(group, stage, table: list[TableRow])`.\n\n**Critical correctness point:** a WC2026 fixture's pre-match form/rest/Elo must reflect **all prior football**, not just other WC fixtures. So build the issue-#9 assembler over the **full** chronologically-sorted history, then **filter** the resulting frame to WC2026 rows \u2014 this preserves correct `before_idx` (no-leakage) semantics. Do NOT run the builder on the WC2026 subset alone.\n\nReuse the same `EloResult`/`TeamAbilities` the caller already computed (DI) \u2014 no recompute. `data.elo.seed_wc2026(result, teams)` is available if pre-tournament Elo for not-yet-seen teams is needed.\n\n**Scope guard:** consume Elo/Poisson (Cycle 2), reuse the issue-#9 assembler (no duplicate covariate logic), no model/training (Cycle 4), no Monte Carlo/backtest (Cycle 5). Football-only.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Given an in-memory martj42 frame containing unplayed `FIFA World Cup` rows, `wc2026_features(...)` returns those rows with the full feature schema and `home_goals`/`away_goals` as `<NA>`.\n- [ ] WC2026 fixture features equal what the full-history issue-#9 builder produces for the same rows (consistency \u2014 a single covariate code path, proven by comparing the filtered subset to the full build).\n- [ ] `live_fixtures_to_df(state)` maps a list of `LiveMatch` to the exact martj42 results column set/dtypes (passes `validate_results_df`), sets `TOURNAMENT=\"FIFA World Cup\"`, `<NA>` goals for remaining fixtures, and **drops `None`-team placeholder slots**.\n- [ ] The entire suite runs with **no network** \u2014 the live path is exercised only via constructed `TournamentState`/`LiveMatch` objects (mirroring `tests/test_live_adapter.py`).\n- [ ] No-key path produces a usable WC2026 frame without any API key.\n- [ ] Deterministic given the seed.\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #7: feat: static confederation map + FIFA-ranking fallback resolver + [features_build] config\n- #9: feat: core per-match feature assembler over martj42 history\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/features/wc2026.py`\n  - `wc2026_features(results_df, *, config, elo, abilities, ranking=None) -> pd.DataFrame` \u2014 run the issue-#9 builder on the **full** `results_df` (sorted), then filter to `wc2026_schedule` rows; return only the WC2026 subset.\n  - `live_fixtures_to_df(state: TournamentState, *, include_played: bool = False) -> pd.DataFrame` \u2014 convert `remaining_group_fixtures` (and optionally `played`) `LiveMatch` objects into the martj42 results schema: `DATE` from `utc_date[:10]`, `HOME_TEAM`/`AWAY_TEAM` already normalized, goals `<NA>` for remaining, `TOURNAMENT=\"FIFA World Cup\"`, `NEUTRAL` per the WC2026 (host-cities-neutral) convention. Drop fixtures with `None` teams.\n  - Thin documented wrapper around `data.elo.seed_wc2026` if pre-tournament Elo seeding is needed for not-yet-seen teams.\n- **Modify:** none (exports wired by the final exports task).\n- **Create:** `tests/test_features_wc2026.py` \u2014 BDD naming; in-memory martj42 frame with unplayed WC rows; constructed `TournamentState`/`LiveMatch` (incl. a `None`-team placeholder to assert it is dropped); assert schema-identity with the issue-#9 build and `validate_results_df` passes. No network/I/O.\n- Conventions: `from __future__ import annotations`; `|` unions; `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)`; reuse the existing assembler \u2014 do not duplicate covariate logic; mypy strict; ruff line-length 100.",
