tch_diffs[i]` aligns positionally with `sorted_df.iloc[i]`. Add a **per-row alignment guard** asserting `(diff.home_team, diff.away_team, diff.date) == (row.HOME_TEAM, row.AWAY_TEAM, row.DATE)` and raise a clear `ValueError` on drift rather than silently emit leaked features. All time-aware helpers are called with `before_idx=i` so a match never sees its own or later results.\n\n**Scope guard:** consume Elo/Poisson \u2014 do NOT recompute or refit them in `build()`. No model training / `[rf]` (Cycle 4), no Monte Carlo/backtest (Cycle 5). **Football-only:** no socio-economic/market-value/GDP/odds columns ever appear in the output.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Output frame has exactly one row per input match (including unplayed WC2026 rows) with a stable, documented column set; labels (`home_goals`/`away_goals`) pass through as `<NA>` for unplayed.\n- [ ] **Football-only allow-list test:** the exact output column set is asserted \u2014 no GDP/market-value/odds fields present.\n- [ ] `elo_diff == home_elo - away_elo` for every row (consumed, not recomputed); attack/defence columns equal the values in a hand-built `TeamAbilities` passed in (proves no refit).\n- [ ] Neutral flag round-trips exactly from the input `NEUTRAL` column.\n- [ ] A constructed two-match history shows match-2 features using only match-1 information (end-to-end no-leakage test).\n- [ ] Misaligned Elo/df input raises `ValueError` (alignment-guard test).\n- [ ] Confederation columns are deterministically encoded over the six `CONFEDERATIONS` indicators; a `None` ranking degrades to confederation without breaking the frame.\n- [ ] Deterministic given `FeatureBuildConfig.random_seed`.\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #7: feat: static confederation map + FIFA-ranking fallback resolver + [features_build] config\n- #8: feat: time-aware recent-form, rest-days, and goal-difference helpers\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/features/build.py`\n  - Frozen dataclass `MatchFeatures` (the `FittedDistribution`/`MatchEloDiff`-style record): `date, home_team, away_team, neutral, home_elo, away_elo, elo_diff, home_attack, home_defence, away_attack, away_defence, home_form, away_form, home_rest_days: float | None, away_rest_days: float | None, home_goal_diff, away_goal_diff, home_confederation: str | None, away_confederation: str | None, home_ranking: float | None, away_ranking: float | None, home_goals: int | None, away_goals: int | None`. As a pure data record it may exceed the 50-line class budget (same exemption as `MatchEloDiff`).\n  - `FeatureBuilder(config: FeatureBuildConfig, *, ranking=None, confed_map=CONFEDERATION_MAP)` with `build(df, elo, abilities) -> list[MatchFeatures]` and `build_frame(df, elo, abilities) -> pd.DataFrame`. Keep methods < 10 lines by delegating to the issue-#7/#8 helpers.\n  - `to_frame(rows: list[MatchFeatures]) -> pd.DataFrame` \u2014 tidy output; deterministic one-hot of the two confederation columns into the six indicators (fixed column order).\n  - Module-level factory `build_features(df, config=None, *, ranking=None) -> pd.DataFrame` \u2014 convenience that calls `compute_elo` + `fit_dixon_coles` once when the caller does not supply them; the primary `build()` accepts pre-computed `EloResult`/`TeamAbilities` (DI, no recompute when shared across historical + WC2026 frames).\n- **Modify:** none (exports wired by the final exports task).\n- **Create:** `tests/test_features_build.py` \u2014 BDD naming; in-memory martj42-shaped frames; pass a hand-built `TeamAbilities` and a real `compute_elo` result; assert the allow-list, alignment guard (`ValueError`), no-leakage, neutral round-trip, determinism. No network/I/O.\n- Conventions: `from __future__ import annotations`; module-level pure helpers above the class; `|` unions; `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)`; mypy strict; ruff line-length 100.",
